content.description: On the north side of Coffee Cake. The mid section gets a little thin.  With your left on the big jug and right hand on the chicken head, use a high left foot into a pocket to move up to a slim smoothish crimp. Once to the top, top out either left or right.
Start low, then follow the crack up. Top out. Can climb down on the trail side.
content.protection: Multiple pads a plus, as well as a spotter.
content.location: West face of Coffe Cake Boulder. Look for the crack on the left side of the west face.

content.description: Start between the two large "holes" in the face.  There are two thumb depressions about chest high for start holds.  Climb up between the depressions and work slightly right to top out at the large crack between the two rocks on top of the route.  Its got a little too much angle to need too much balance, but is a fun and different climb than the others on this boulder.

Same start as arachnid, but go straight up and top out. Start with both hands in the large pocket that is just past where the rock transitions from black to orange. Pull yourself up over the small roof, stand up, and top out. Climb down on the trail side.
content.location: Pretty much dead center on the west face of Coffe Cake.

content.description: Start from the obvious chalk marks.  Go straight up and over the outcrop.  Find the right-hand pinch!
content.protection: Pads and a friend to spot
content.location: Northwest corner of Coffee Cake.  Left of the crack (Speedy Shoes).

content.description: Two hand start on the jug, go straight up avoiding the left corner. Once near the top, top out to the left.
Start in the back left.  Work your fingers through the roof in pockets, moving your feet until you can reach out to the rail on the lip.  Cut feet and rock up on a right heel to top out.
content.location: Northeast corner of Coffee Cake.  Visible from Coyote Cave trail.

content.description: Stary right hand in the large pocket, left in the crack.  Straight up through powerful moves to a slopey top out.
content.protection: Definitely need pads and a spotter helps too.
content.location: Immediately to the right of Speedy Shoes.

content.description: Start with both hands in the large pocket that is just past where the rock transitions from black to orange. Pull yourself up over the small roof, stand up, and top out. Climb down on the trail side.
content.location: Pretty much dead center on the west face of Coffe Cake.

content.description: A bit of a highball, but the west side has a series of stair step ledges at the top for a slightly shorter top out.
